                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 14.797,
                                "byte_start": 91014,
                                "byte_stop": 150260,
                                "text": "The opinion of the Court in No. 90-1419, National Railroad Passenger Corporation versus Boston and Maine Corporation and a companion case will be announced by Justice Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 14.797,
                        "stop": 177.946,
                        "byte_start": 150260,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15113,
                            "name": "Anthony M. Kennedy",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/anthony_m_kennedy",
                            "last_name": "Kennedy",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2757,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 572162400,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2757"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32679,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 47100,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/anthony_kennedy_1_3.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 10147,
                            "identifier": "anthony_m_kennedy"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 14.797,
                                "stop": 26.984,
                                "byte_start": 150260,
                                "byte_stop": 198952,
                                "text": "These cases involve the Railroad Passenger Service Act of 1970 and that Act created a corporation called the National Railroad Passenger Corporation but it is better known as Amtrak."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 26.984,
                                "stop": 35.217,
                                "byte_start": 198952,
                                "byte_stop": 231971,
                                "text": "Amtrak\u0027s purpose is to provide inner city rail passenger service and it, along with the Interstate Commerce Commission are the petitioners in these consolidated cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 35.217,
                                "stop": 40.614,
                                "byte_start": 231971,
                                "byte_stop": 253496,
                                "text": "The case has raised questions regarding the proper interpretation of an imminent domain provision in the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 40.614,
                                "stop": 46.702,
                                "byte_start": 253496,
                                "byte_stop": 277842,
                                "text": "Amtrak\u0027s Montrealer train service operates between Washington D.C. and Montreal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 46.702,
                                "stop": 55.474,
                                "byte_start": 277842,
                                "byte_stop": 312950,
                                "text": "For part of the way, the train at one time operated on railroad tracks owned by the Boston and Maine Corporation, and Boston and Maine as a respondent in these cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 55.474,
                                "stop": 67.403,
                                "byte_start": 312950,
                                "byte_stop": 360702,
                                "text": "In the early 1980s, Amtrak ran into difficulties with the Montrealer service which eventually forced it to cancel the service and Amtrak claims that poor maintenance of its tracks by Boston and Maine was the cause of the problem."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 67.403,
                                "stop": 74.086,
                                "byte_start": 360702,
                                "byte_stop": 387452,
                                "text": "Amtrak then reached an agreement with Central Vermont Railroad, another petitioner here and a competitor of Boston and Maine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 74.086,
                                "stop": 85.228,
                                "byte_start": 387452,
                                "byte_stop": 431964,
                                "text": "Under that agreement, Amtrak was to acquire Boston and Maine\u0027s tracks and transfer them to Central Vermont in exchange for the use of the track and a promise from Central Vermont to properly maintain them."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 85.228,
                                "stop": 91.638,
                                "byte_start": 431964,
                                "byte_stop": 457669,
                                "text": "Amtrak requested and received a condemnation order from the ICC pursuant to an imminent domain provision in the Act."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 91.638,
                                "stop": 105.446,
                                "byte_start": 457669,
                                "byte_stop": 512839,
                                "text": "We granted certiorari to the Court of Appeals for the District of Columbia Circuit after that court held that the relevant section of the Act does not permit condemnation of the property which Amtrak intends to convey to a third party following condemnation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 105.446,
                                "stop": 110.32,
                                "byte_start": 512839,
                                "byte_stop": 532379,
                                "text": "And the court held that rejecting a contra-interpretation of the ICC."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 110.32,
                                "stop": 117.939,
                                "byte_start": 532379,
                                "byte_stop": 562785,
                                "text": "After the Court of Appeals\u0027 decision, Congress amended the statute to add a sentence stating that Amtrak was authorized to re-convey condemned property."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 117.939,
                                "stop": 123.274,
                                "byte_start": 562785,
                                "byte_stop": 584206,
                                "text": "The Court of Appeals, nonetheless, denied rehearing holding that the amendment did not affect its reasoning."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.274,
                                "stop": 127.807,
                                "byte_start": 584206,
                                "byte_stop": 602283,
                                "text": "The ICC\u0027s condemnation order was based on the agency\u0027s interpretation of the controlling statute."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 127.807,
                                "stop": 134.886,
                                "byte_start": 602283,
                                "byte_stop": 630599,
                                "text": "The agency relied on the statutory presumption of need to conclude that Amtrak had established its entitlement to the order."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.886,
                                "stop": 148.032,
                                "byte_start": 630599,
                                "byte_stop": 683158,
                                "text": "In so doing the ICC implicitly adapted an interpretation of the statute and that which Amtrak was permitted to make a judgment regarding its need for the property sought so long as the property would be used in Amtrak\u0027s rail operations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 148.032,
                                "stop": 157.22,
                                "byte_start": 683158,
                                "byte_stop": 719938,
                                "text": "We hold today that the ICC\u0027s was a reasonable interpretation of the condemnation provision in the statute and therefore, the Court of Appeals erred in setting aside the ICC order."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.22,
                                "stop": 168.191,
                                "byte_start": 719938,
                                "byte_stop": 763824,
                                "text": "The ICC is the agency charged with the administration of the statute and under our well-settled doctrine, the ICC\u0027s interpretation of that provision is entitled to great deference from the reviewing court\u0027s."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 168.191,
                                "stop": 172.769,
                                "byte_start": 763824,
                                "byte_stop": 782110,
                                "text": "The judgment of he Court of Appeals is reversed and the case is remanded for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.769,
                                "stop": 177.946,
                                "byte_start": 782110,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice White has filed a dissenting opinion in which Justices Blackmun and Thomas join."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
